Description: Up for auction is this drop dead gorgeous 2005 American Deluxe Stratocaster. The body is contoured Solid Ash and is finished in a near flawless Transparent Butterscotch. The guitar is in 'Mint' condition, with no discernible scratches, dents, mars, or marks of wear on it. To start, the Pickups, the Volume and Tone controls are in Black, The Pick Guard and Trem Spring plate covers are single ply heavy gauge Black. The pickups are Samarian Cobalt Noiseless. This guitar also features S-1 Tone Switching, accessed by a push/push button on the cap of the Volume Control. This give you even further tone and pickup combinations than the standard 5 way pickup selector switch. The bridge is fully adjustable with 6 solid bridge pieces as used on the current Elite series, and features Fender's 2 Point Tremolo with a pop in Tremolo bar. On the contoured back, there are no discernible scratches or marks of any kind. The heel plate has Micro Tilt Allen wrench access. The Maple neck is a modern 'C' shape with a Bi-Flex Adjustable Truss Rod. The fingerboard is a medium colored Rosewood with 22 Medium Jumbo highly detailed frets, rolled edges, and Inlaid Abalone dot fingerboard markers. And up top, the Tuning Machines are Fender polished locking machines. This guitar comes complete with it's Pop-in Tremolo bar, Strap Locks, Allen Adjusting wrenches, Fender Strap, cord connector, S-1 Switch guide, original shop assembly tag, hang tags, and it's original molded hard shell case. Please feel free to ask any questions. And If you think I am overstating the quality of this instrument, please look at my 100% seller ratings and buyer feedback to understand you are bidding on an instrument of the highest quality. Good luck in your bidding!
